{
  "texts": [
    "Each method in the class represents a distinct capability: 'think()' for planning, 'act()' for tool invocation, 'observe()' for data analysis, and 'respond()' for synthesis.",
    "This modular structure makes it easy to understand how each component contributes to the agent's overall intelligence and allows researchers to extend the agent with additional tools or more sophisticated reasoning capabilities.Several features of the code above are worth emphasizing.",
    "First, it is fully vibe-coded -coding agents are capable of writing simple programs like this in less than a minute.",
    "The code is also structured in a clean and easily legible manner with clear documentation.",
    "Second, a significant part of the code consists of natural language instructions to the LLM."
  ]
}